(liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n12\t | `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. Also defines the `CustomerId`/`Metric` anchored-allowlist `constr` types reused by `schemas/usage.py` and `schemas/usage_export.py`. |\n13\t | `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n14\t | `schemas/usage_export.py` | `UsageExportQueryParams` for GET /v1/usage/export — optional `customer_id`/`metric`/`from`/`to` filters (`from` bound via a Pydantic alias to the `from_` field, since `from` is a Python keyword), the same `[now-90d, now+1h]` range bound as `usage.py`, `extra='forbid'`. |\n15\t-| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |\n16\t+| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for `/v1/quotas`: `QuotaPutRequest` (PUT body: `customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`), `QuotaResponse` (PUT/GET response echo shape, minimal field set), and `QuotaDeleteParams` (DELETE query params: `customer_id`, `metric`, reusing the same anchored `CustomerId`/`Metric` allowlists as `QuotaPutRequest`, `extra='forbid'`). |\n17\t | `csv_export.py` | The CSV encoding facade for the export route: `EXPORT_HEADER`, `escape_csv_text_cell` (the OWASP CSV/formula-injection escape, applied at the encoding sink independent of upstream ingest validation), and the `format_window_start`/`format_total_quantity` value formatters. |\n18\t-| `middleware.py` | Request-ID / trace-ID assignment, security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options), CORS (allows GET/POST/PUT). |\n19\t+| `middleware.py` | Request-ID / trace-ID assignment, security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options), CORS (allows GET/POST/PUT/DELETE). |\n20\t | `errors.py` | Error-envelope boundary: catches all unhandled exceptions and returns `{error:{code,message,requestId}}` with no stack/secret leakage. `AppError` lets a raised exception carry an explicit `app_code` (e.g. `quota_exceeded`) that overrides the default status->code map — needed because 429 is shared by two distinct codes (`rate_limited` vs `quota_exceeded`). |\n21\t \n22\t ## Relationships\n23\t@@ -53,11 +53,13 @@ HTTP API layer: FastAPI route handlers, request/response schemas (Pydantic v2),\n24\t - `quantity` is a decimal > 0 (no zero or negative); `idempotency_key` is alphanumeric + underscore/dash.\n25\t - GET `/v1/usage` requires a timezone-aware ISO-8601 `window` parameter within 90 days past to 1 hour future (naive datetimes rejected).\n26\t - PUT `/v1/quotas`: `limit_per_window` is an integer `>= 1` (`<= 1e15`, BIGINT-safe); `customer_id`/`metric` reuse the same anchored allowlists as events; unknown fields (including a client-supplied `api_key_id`/`scope`) are rejected outright.\n27\t+- GET `/v1/quotas` accepts no body/query/path parameter (full, unpaginated list of the caller's tenant); DELETE `/v1/quotas` takes `customer_id`/`metric` as **query parameters** (`QuotaDeleteParams`), reusing PUT's exact same anchored allowlists; unknown query params (including a client-supplied `api_key_id`) are rejected outright.\n28\t - GET `/v1/usage/export`: every filter (`customer_id`, `metric`, `from`, `to`) is optional; `from`/`to` follow the same timezone-aware, `[now-90d, now+1h]`-bounded contract as `usage.py`'s `window`, plus `from <= to`; unknown query params (including a client-supplied `api_key_id`) are rejected outright. A result exceeding 100,000 rows is rejected 422 *before* any response byte (a pre-flight `COUNT`, not a mid-stream cutoff).\n29\t \n30\t **Error handling:**\n31\t - Authentication failures (missing/invalid key) → 401/403 before handlers run.\n32\t-- `PUT /v1/quotas` from a non-`admin`-scoped key → 403 `forbidden` (function-level authorization, checked in the route's composed dependency).\n33\t+- `PUT`/`GET`/`DELETE /v1/quotas` from a non-`admin`-scoped key → 403 `forbidden` (function-level authorization, checked in the route's shared `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency).\n34\t+- `DELETE /v1/quotas` for a `(customer_id, metric)` not present in the caller's tenant → 404 `not_found` (explicit, not silently idempotent); a cross-tenant delete attempt is indistinguishable from this (matches zero rows under the `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS).\n35\t - Rate-limit exceeded (Tier-1 or Tier-2) → 429 `rate_limited` + Retry-After header.\n36\t - `POST /v1/events` over its quota → 429 `quota_exceeded` (distinct code, same status) + Retry-After to the next hour boundary; no event/rollup written (transaction rolled back).\n37\t - Schema validation failure → 422 with Pydantic error detail.\n38\tdiff --git a/src/api/middleware.py b/src/api/middleware.py\n39\tindex f21399c..7b6f60b 100644\n40\t--- a/src/api/middleware.py\n41\t+++ b/src/api/middleware.py\n42\t@@ -160,6 +160,6 @@ def configure_cors(app: FastAPI, settings: Settings) -> None:\n43\t         CORSMiddleware,\n44\t         allow_origins=list(settings.cors_allowed_origins),\n45\t         allow_credentials=False,\n46\t-        allow_methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\"],\n47\t+        allow_methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"],\n48\t         allow_headers=[\"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"Idempotency-Key\"],\n49\t     )\n50\tdiff --git a/src/api/routes/quotas.py b/src/api/routes/quotas.py\n51\tindex 2443d41..b31d62b 100644\n52\t--- a/src/api/routes/quotas.py\n53\t+++ b/src/api/routes/quotas.py\n54\t@@ -1,21 +1,30 @@\n55\t-\"\"\"`PUT /v1/quotas` — admin-scoped create-or-replace of a per-customer,\n56\t-per-metric usage cap.\n57\t+\"\"\"`/v1/quotas` — admin-scoped create-or-replace (`PUT`), list (`GET`), and\n58\t+remove (`DELETE`) of a per-customer, per-metric usage cap.\n59\t \n60\t Edge behavior (security headers, CORS, body-size guard, Tier-1 throttle) is\n61\t-inherited from the middleware stack; this route wires\n62\t+inherited from the middleware stack; every route on this router wires\n63\t auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> admin-scope check -> schema validation -> service,\n64\t mirroring the `events`/`usage` routes' sibling `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`\n65\t-pattern (kept per-route, not shared, per the existing convention).\n66\t+pattern (kept per-route, not shared, per the existing convention). All three\n67\t+verbs depend on the same `_require_admin_and_throttled` chain — GET/DELETE\n68\t+reuse it verbatim rather than introducing a new scope or auth path.\n69\t \"\"\"\n70\t \n71\t-from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, Request, Response, status\n72\t+from typing import Annotated\n73\t \n74\t-from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n75\t+from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, Query, Request, Response, status\n76\t+\n77\t+from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaDeleteParams, QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n78\t from src.auth import require_api_key\n79\t from src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n80\t from src.auth.rate_limit import enforce_tier2_rate_limit\n81\t from src.logging import get_logger\n82\t-from src.services.quota_service import to_response, upsert_tenant_quota\n83\t+from src.services.quota_service import (\n84\t+    delete_tenant_quota,\n85\t+    list_tenant_quotas,\n86\t+    to_response,\n87\t+    upsert_tenant_quota,\n88\t+)\n89\t \n90\t router = APIRouter(tags=[\"quotas\"])\n91\t logger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n92\t@@ -54,3 +63,25 @@ async def put_quota(\n93\t     outcome = await upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)\n94\t     response.status_code = outcome.http_status\n95\t     return to_response(outcome)\n96\t+\n97\t+\n98\t+@router.get(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=list[QuotaResponse])\n99\t+async def list_quotas_endpoint(\n100\t+    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n101\t+) -> list[QuotaResponse]:\n102\t+    \"\"\"Return the caller's own tenant's full, unpaginated quota list,\n103\t+    deterministically ordered by `(customer_id, metric)`. An empty tenant\n104\t+    gets `200 []`, never a 404.\"\"\"\n105\t+    return await list_tenant_quotas(principal)\n106\t+\n107\t+\n108\t+@router.delete(\"/v1/quotas\", status_code=status.HTTP_204_NO_CONTENT)\n109\t+async def delete_quota_endpoint(\n110\t+    params: Annotated[QuotaDeleteParams, Query()],\n111\t+    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n112\t+) -> Response:\n113\t+    \"\"\"Remove the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the caller's own\n114\t+    tenant — 204 on success, 404 if no such quota exists in this tenant\n115\t+    (explicit, not silently idempotent).\"\"\"\n116\t+    await delete_tenant_quota(principal, params)\n117\t+    return Response(status_code=status.HTTP_204_NO_CONTENT)\n118\tdiff --git a/src/api/schemas/quotas.py b/src/api/schemas/quotas.py\n119\tindex d1270ff..3fcd099 100644\n120\t--- a/src/api/schemas/quotas.py\n121\t+++ b/src/api/schemas/quotas.py\n122\t@@ -45,3 +45,19 @@ class QuotaResponse(BaseModel):\n123\t     customer_id: str\n124\t     metric: str\n125\t     limit_per_window: int\n126\t+\n127\t+\n128\t+class QuotaDeleteParams(BaseModel):\n129\t+    \"\"\"The two required query parameters of `DELETE /v1/quotas`, reusing the\n130\t+    exact same anchored `CustomerId`/`Metric` allowlists `QuotaPutRequest`\n131\t+    validates against — same identifiers, same sinks, same rejection\n132\t+    behavior (422). `extra='forbid'` rejects any unknown query param\n133\t+    (including a client-supplied `api_key_id`), the mass-assignment defense\n134\t+    that keeps the delete target's tenant resolved only from the\n135\t+    authenticated principal (ASVS 15.3.3).\n136\t+    \"\"\"\n137\t+\n138\t+    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n139\t+\n140\t+    customer_id: CustomerId\n141\t+    metric: Metric\n142\tdiff --git a/src/repositories/README.md b/src/repositories/README.md\n143\tindex fb6b4da..fdb474f 100644\n144\t--- a/src/repositories/README.md\n145\t+++ b/src/repositories/README.md\n146\t@@ -11,14 +11,14 @@ Data access layer: SQL queries with parameterization, row-level scoping (by auth\n147\t | `events_repo.py` | `insert_event_if_new(session, *, api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start)` — `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, idempotency_key) DO NOTHING`, returning `None` on a duplicate. `find_event_by_idempotency_key(session, *, api_key_id, idempotency_key)` — reads back the original row on a duplicate replay. `increment_usage_rollup(session, *, api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window_start, quantity)` — the rollup upsert, called only after `insert_event_if_new` returns a row. |\n148\t | `usage_repo.py` | `find_usage_rollup(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window_start)` — SELECT from `usage_rollup` scoped by `api_key_id`. Returns None if missing (caller handles zero conversion). `count_usage_rollups(api_key_id, customer_id=None, metric=None, window_from=None, window_to=None)` — the export's pre-flight row-cap count over the same optional filters. `stream_usage_rollups(api_key_id, ..., limit)` — the export's server-side-cursor stream (`session.stream(...)`, yields `UsageRollupExportRecord`), ordered by a **fixed literal** `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric` (never client-derived) with `LIMIT`. The count and stream queries share a `_export_filter_clause_and_params` helper so their WHERE clauses can never drift apart. |\n149\t | `api_keys_repo.py` | `find_active_key_by_key_id(key_id)` — SELECT from `api_keys` by public `key_id` (used by auth cache miss); returns the full row including `scope`. `create_api_key(..., scope=\"ingest\")` — the only key-provisioning path. |\n150\t-| `quotas_repo.py` | `upsert_quota(...)` — `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0) AS inserted`, reporting create-vs-replace in one round-trip. `read_tenant_quota_state_locked(...)` — the atomic check-then-decide: locks the quota row (`FOR UPDATE`), then reads the current-window rollup total as a **separate, fresh** statement (see *Notes* below for why). Returns `None` when no quota exists (unlimited, no lock taken). |\n151\t+| `quotas_repo.py` | `upsert_quota(...)` — `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0) AS inserted`, reporting create-vs-replace in one round-trip. `read_tenant_quota_state_locked(...)` — the atomic check-then-decide: locks the quota row (`FOR UPDATE`), then reads the current-window rollup total as a **separate, fresh** statement (see *Notes* below for why). Returns `None` when no quota exists (unlimited, no lock taken). `list_quotas(session, *, api_key_id)` — `api_key_id`-scoped `SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window ... ORDER BY customer_id, metric` (index-friendly on the table's PK prefix), returns `list[QuotaListItem]`. `delete_quota(session, *, api_key_id, customer_id, metric)` — parameterized `DELETE ... WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric = :metric RETURNING customer_id`, returns `bool` (whether a row matched and was removed). |\n152\t \n153\t ## Relationships\n154\t \n155\t **Public surface:**\n156\t - Imported by `src/services.{events_service, usage_service, usage_export_service, quota_service}` to execute queries.\n157\t - `api_keys_repo` is also imported by `src/auth.api_key` (credential lookup on cache miss).\n158\t-- `quotas_repo` is imported by both `quota_service` (the upsert) and `events_service` (the read-and-decide).\n159\t+- `quotas_repo` is imported by `quota_service` (the upsert, list, and delete) and `events_service` (the read-and-decide).\n160\t \n161\t **Dependencies:**\n162\t - All functions are async; they receive an `AsyncSession` from the service layer (obtained via `src/db.session_context`).\n163\t@@ -34,6 +34,7 @@ Data access layer: SQL queries with parameterization, row-level scoping (by auth\n164\t **Field projections (minimal surface):**\n165\t - `insert_event_if_new` / `find_event_by_idempotency_key` return an `EventRecord{id, api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start}` — the service layer maps this to the minimal public response shape (not the full row is a service-layer concern, not a repo-layer projection).\n166\t - `find_usage_rollup` returns only `{total_quantity, event_count}` — not internal bookkeeping (`updated_at`, `api_key_id`).\n167\t+- `list_quotas` returns `QuotaListItem{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}` — the same minimal shape `QuotaResponse` echoes, never `api_key_id`/timestamps.\n168\t - `stream_usage_rollups` yields `UsageRollupExportRecord{customer_id, metric, window_start, total_quantity}` — exactly the four exported columns, never `event_count`, `updated_at`, or `api_key_id`.\n169\t - `api_keys_repo.get_by_key_id` returns the full row (needed by auth for `secret_hash`, `rate_limit_per_sec`, `revoked_at`).\n170\t \n171\t@@ -48,6 +49,11 @@ Data access layer: SQL queries with parameterization, row-level scoping (by auth\n172\t - If the unique constraint is violated, the INSERT returns no rows.\n173\t - The service layer checks `if result` — if a row was returned, this request won the insert; if not, a duplicate is detected.\n174\t \n175\t+**DELETE ... RETURNING pattern:**\n176\t+- `delete_quota` issues a single parameterized `DELETE ... WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric = :metric RETURNING customer_id`.\n177\t+- Whether a row was returned (not a row-count check) is what the service uses to distinguish \"removed\" from \"nothing there to remove\" — avoids a separate existence check and the TOCTOU gap that would introduce between check and delete.\n178\t+- A cross-tenant call matches zero rows here (the `api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS backstop), which the service maps to the same 404 as a truly-absent quota — the BOLA-safe behavior.\n179\t+\n180\t **RLS context setup:**\n181\t - Before any query, `src/db.session_context` sets `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :id` in the transaction.\n182\t - This context variable is read by the PostgreSQL RLS policy on every table access.\n183\tdiff --git a/src/repositories/quotas_repo.py b/src/repositories/quotas_repo.py\n184\tindex 52e9394..9578be4 100644\n185\t--- a/src/repositories/quotas_repo.py\n186\t+++ b/src/repositories/quotas_repo.py\n187\t@@ -36,6 +36,15 @@ class QuotaState:\n188\t     current_total: Decimal\n189\t \n190\t \n191\t+@dataclass(frozen=True)\n192\t+class QuotaListItem:\n193\t+    \"\"\"One row of `GET /v1/quotas`'s listing — the minimal, public quota shape.\"\"\"\n194\t+\n195\t+    customer_id: str\n196\t+    metric: str\n197\t+    limit_per_window: int\n198\t+\n199\t+\n200\t async def upsert_quota(\n201\t     session: AsyncSession,\n202\t     *,\n203\t@@ -147,3 +156,60 @@ async def read_tenant_quota_state_locked(\n204\t     rollup_row = rollup_result.mappings().first()\n205\t     current_total = rollup_row[\"total_quantity\"] if rollup_row is not None else Decimal(0)\n206\t     return QuotaState(limit_per_window=lock_row[\"limit_per_window\"], current_total=Decimal(current_total))\n207\t+\n208\t+\n209\t+async def list_quotas(session: AsyncSession, *, api_key_id: int) -> list[QuotaListItem]:\n210\t+    \"\"\"Return every quota row for the caller's own tenant, ordered by\n211\t+    `(customer_id, metric)` for a deterministic, repeatable listing.\n212\t+\n213\t+    The `ORDER BY` matches the leading columns of the table's primary key\n214\t+    `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`, so the sort is index-friendly on top\n215\t+    of the already-scoped index scan (plan §\"deterministic ORDER BY\").\n216\t+    \"\"\"\n217\t+    result = await session.execute(\n218\t+        text(\n219\t+            \"\"\"\n220\t+            SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window\n221\t+            FROM quotas\n222\t+            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id\n223\t+            ORDER BY customer_id, metric\n224\t+            \"\"\"\n225\t+        ),\n226\t+        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id},\n227\t+    )\n228\t+    return [\n229\t+        QuotaListItem(\n230\t+            customer_id=row[\"customer_id\"],\n231\t+            metric=row[\"metric\"],\n232\t+            limit_per_window=row[\"limit_per_window\"],\n233\t+        )\n234\t+        for row in result.mappings().all()\n235\t+    ]\n236\t+\n237\t+\n238\t+async def delete_quota(\n239\t+    session: AsyncSession, *, api_key_id: int, customer_id: str, metric: str\n240\t+) -> bool:\n241\t+    \"\"\"Remove the cap for `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`, returning\n242\t+    whether a row actually matched and was removed.\n243\t+\n244\t+    `RETURNING customer_id` on a single-statement, parameterized `DELETE` is\n245\t+    what lets the service distinguish \"removed\" from \"nothing there to\n246\t+    remove\" without a separate existence check (avoiding a TOCTOU gap\n247\t+    between check and delete). The explicit `api_key_id` filter is the\n248\t+    primary tenant-confinement control; `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE RLS\n249\t+    (migration `0003`) is the backstop — a cross-tenant call matches zero\n250\t+    rows here, which the service maps to 404 (plan §\"Tenant confinement is\n251\t+    structural, not a special case\").\n252\t+    \"\"\"\n253\t+    result = await session.execute(\n254\t+        text(\n255\t+            \"\"\"\n256\t+            DELETE FROM quotas\n257\t+            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric = :metric\n258\t+            RETURNING customer_id\n259\t+            \"\"\"\n260\t+        ),\n261\t+        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id, \"customer_id\": customer_id, \"metric\": metric},\n262\t+    )\n263\t+    return result.mappings().first() is not None\n264\tdiff --git a/src/services/README.md b/src/services/README.md\n265\tindex c7aacf6..8ce7cfc 100644\n266\t--- a/src/services/README.md\n267\t+++ b/src/services/README.md\n268\t@@ -11,7 +11,7 @@ Business logic layer: event ingestion (with idempotency and counter atomicity),\n269\t | `events_service.py` | `create_event(principal, payload)` — inserts an event, checks the caller's quota (if any) on the winning-insert branch, and increments the hourly counter, all in one transaction; idempotent on `idempotency_key`. Raises `QuotaExceededError` (429 `quota_exceeded`) when `R + Q > L`, which rolls back the event insert. Returns the created/replayed event. |\n270\t | `usage_service.py` | `get_usage(principal, query)` — reads the aggregated counter for the `(customer_id, metric, window)` bucket in `query` (a `UsageQueryParams`); returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n271\t | `usage_export_service.py` | `prepare_export(principal, params)` — the pre-flight row-cap check: a `COUNT(*)` in its own transaction, raising a plain 422 `HTTPException` over `MAX_EXPORT_ROWS` (100,000) *before* any response byte; any other (non-cap) error propagates uncaught to the error-envelope boundary (fail-closed 500, no stream ever started). `stream_export_csv(principal, params)` — the `StreamingResponse` body generator: opens its own tenant-scoped transaction (Starlette pulls it only after the route returns), yields the header row first always (so an empty result is a 200 header-only CSV, never 404), then one CSV-encoded row per streamed rollup at constant memory (a reused `io.StringIO`, drained and reset per row), and logs one `usage.export` audit event in a `finally` block (fires even on a client disconnect or a mid-stream error). |\n272\t-| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. |\n273\t+| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. `list_tenant_quotas(principal)` — opens a `scoped_transaction`, calls `quotas_repo.list_quotas`, and maps the rows to `list[QuotaResponse]`; an empty tenant gets an empty list (no dedicated business log — a plain read of the caller's own config, mirroring `usage_service.get_usage`). `delete_tenant_quota(principal, params)` — opens a `scoped_transaction`, calls `quotas_repo.delete_quota`; raises `HTTPException(404)` if no row matched, otherwise logs the `quota.delete` audit event. |\n274\t | `time_windows.py` | `floor_to_hour_utc(timestamp: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by `events_service` and `usage_service`. |\n275\t \n276\t ## Relationships\n277\t@@ -23,8 +23,8 @@ Business logic layer: event ingestion (with idempotency and counter atomicity),\n278\t - `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, quotas_repo}` to insert the event, check the quota, and upsert the counter.\n279\t - `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n280\t - `usage_export_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` (`count_usage_rollups`, `stream_usage_rollups`) and `src/api/csv_export.py` (the column contract + formula-escape facade) — it owns the `csv.writer`/`io.StringIO` streaming mechanics, `csv_export.py` owns only the encoding/escaping contract.\n281\t-- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert the cap.\n282\t-- All services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT /v1/quotas` at the route layer before `quota_service` ever runs (the export has no scope gate — any authenticated key may export its own tenant's data).\n283\t+- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert, list, and delete quota rows.\n284\t+- All services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT`/`GET`/`DELETE /v1/quotas` at the route layer (via the shared `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency) before `quota_service` ever runs (the export has no scope gate — any authenticated key may export its own tenant's data).\n285\t - `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps.\n286\t \n287\t **Transaction boundary:**\n288\t@@ -33,6 +33,7 @@ Business logic layer: event ingestion (with idempotency and counter atomicity),\n289\t - If the insert loses (duplicate key), the quota is never consulted and neither the counter nor any side effect happens — a no-op.\n290\t - If the quota check rejects (`R + Q > L`), raising `QuotaExceededError` propagates out of the transaction context and rolls it back — the event insert is undone and the counter is never touched (no partial write).\n291\t - `upsert_tenant_quota` wraps the quota upsert in its own transaction; a single `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0)` reports create-vs-replace with no second round-trip.\n292\t+- `list_tenant_quotas` and `delete_tenant_quota` each wrap their query in their own `scoped_transaction`; an unexpected exception inside either propagates to the route's centralized `handle_unexpected_error` boundary and rolls the transaction back — for `delete_tenant_quota` this means a failed DELETE leaves the target row intact (fail-closed, no partial delete).\n293\t \n294\t ## Notes\n295\t \n296\tdiff --git a/src/services/quota_service.py b/src/services/quota_service.py\n297\tindex eb3cc40..40da34c 100644\n298\t--- a/src/services/quota_service.py\n299\t+++ b/src/services/quota_service.py\n300\t@@ -1,18 +1,22 @@\n301\t-\"\"\"Service for `PUT /v1/quotas` — the admin-scoped upsert + 201/200 mapping.\n302\t+\"\"\"Service for `/v1/quotas` — the admin-scoped upsert (`PUT`), list (`GET`),\n303\t+and remove (`DELETE`) operations.\n304\t \n305\t-Orchestrates one transaction per request: the `xmax` upsert in\n306\t-`src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` reports create-vs-replace in a single\n307\t-round-trip, so this layer only maps that to the HTTP status and emits the\n308\t-audit-trail log (`quota.upsert`, plan §\"Repudiation\").\n309\t+Each entry point orchestrates one transaction per request: the `xmax` upsert\n310\t+in `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` reports create-vs-replace in a single\n311\t+round-trip for `PUT`; `GET` opens a read-only scoped transaction for the\n312\t+ordered listing; `DELETE` maps \"no row matched\" to a 404 rather than a\n313\t+silent success (plan §\"DELETE — remove one cap, explicitly\").\n314\t \"\"\"\n315\t \n316\t from dataclasses import dataclass\n317\t \n318\t-from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n319\t+from fastapi import HTTPException, status\n320\t+\n321\t+from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaDeleteParams, QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n322\t from src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n323\t from src.db.session import scoped_transaction\n324\t from src.logging import get_logger\n325\t-from src.repositories.quotas_repo import upsert_quota\n326\t+from src.repositories.quotas_repo import delete_quota, list_quotas, upsert_quota\n327\t \n328\t logger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n329\t \n330\t@@ -69,3 +73,50 @@ def to_response(outcome: QuotaUpsertOutcome) -> QuotaResponse:\n331\t         metric=outcome.metric,\n332\t         limit_per_window=outcome.limit_per_window,\n333\t     )\n334\t+\n335\t+\n336\t+async def list_tenant_quotas(principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal) -> list[QuotaResponse]:\n337\t+    \"\"\"Return the caller's own tenant's full, deterministically ordered quota\n338\t+    list — an empty tenant gets an empty list, never a 404 (plan §\"Empty set\n339\t+    -> 200 [], never 404\"). Deliberately not logged as a business event (open\n340\t+    question 1, resolved default): a plain read of the caller's own\n341\t+    configuration, mirroring `GET /v1/usage`.\n342\t+    \"\"\"\n343\t+    async with scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id) as session:\n344\t+        rows = await list_quotas(session, api_key_id=principal.api_key_id)\n345\t+\n346\t+    return [\n347\t+        QuotaResponse(customer_id=row.customer_id, metric=row.metric, limit_per_window=row.limit_per_window)\n348\t+        for row in rows\n349\t+    ]\n350\t+\n351\t+\n352\t+async def delete_tenant_quota(\n353\t+    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal, params: QuotaDeleteParams\n354\t+) -> None:\n355\t+    \"\"\"Remove the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the caller's own\n356\t+    tenant, raising 404 if no such quota exists (explicit, not silently\n357\t+    idempotent — plan §\"Why 404-on-absent, not idempotent-204\").\n358\t+\n359\t+    A cross-tenant delete attempt matches zero rows (the `api_key_id` filter\n360\t+    + FORCE RLS backstop), which is indistinguishable from a truly-absent\n361\t+    quota — the intended BOLA-safe behavior (threat E2).\n362\t+    \"\"\"\n363\t+    async with scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id) as session:\n364\t+        removed = await delete_quota(\n365\t+            session,\n366\t+            api_key_id=principal.api_key_id,\n367\t+            customer_id=params.customer_id,\n368\t+            metric=params.metric,\n369\t+        )\n370\t+\n371\t+    if not removed:\n372\t+        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND, detail=\"quota not found\")\n373\t+\n374\t+    logger.info(\n375\t+        \"quota.delete\",\n376\t+        userId=principal.api_key_id,\n377\t+        action=\"delete\",\n378\t+        customer_id=params.customer_id,\n379\t+        metric=params.metric,\n380\t+    )\n381\tdiff --git a/tests/README.md b/tests/README.md\n382\tindex 9860087..286c156 100644\n383\t--- a/tests/README.md\n384\t+++ b/tests/README.md\n385\t@@ -22,7 +22,7 @@ unit tests here, endpoint/migration/concurrency/perf tests under `integration/`.\n386\t | `test_logging_redaction.py` | A raw `customer_id` (or other sensitive field) must never reach the rendered log line regardless of call site. |\n387\t | `test_rate_limit_fail_open.py` | Regression test for the Tier-2 rate-limit logging facade in `src/auth/rate_limit.py`. |\n388\t | `test_schemas_events.py` | Validation-contract tests for `EventCreateRequest`. |\n389\t-| `test_schemas_quotas.py` | Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (anchored `customer_id`/`metric` allowlists, `limit_per_window` bounds, injection rejection). |\n390\t+| `test_schemas_quotas.py` | Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (anchored `customer_id`/`metric` allowlists, `limit_per_window` bounds, injection rejection) and `QuotaDeleteParams` (accept/missing/mass-assignment/injection-oversized/invalid-metric cases, plus a Hypothesis property test that acceptance implies the anchored regex). |\n391\t | `test_schemas_usage.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageQueryParams`. |\n392\t | `test_schemas_usage_export.py` | Validation-contract tests for `UsageExportQueryParams`: all-filters-optional, the `from`/`from_` alias binding, naive-datetime rejection, `from<=to` and `[now-90d, now+1h]` bound enforcement, `extra=\"forbid\"` rejecting unknown/injected fields. |\n393\t | `test_slo_alarms_defined.py` | Static assertion that the declared SLO burn-rate + canary CloudWatch alarms exist in the Terraform source with the exact names `deploy.yml` expects. |\n394\tdiff --git a/tests/integration/README.md b/tests/integration/README.md\n395\tindex a19bbec..08c8eda 100644\n396\t--- a/tests/integration/README.md\n397\t+++ b/tests/integration/README.md\n398\t@@ -23,7 +23,8 @@ suite in `tests/` (no live DB/Redis there).\n399\t | `test_quota_concurrency.py` | N concurrent distinct-`idempotency_key` posts against a quota cap `L` never drive the rollup total above `L` (`FOR UPDATE` row-lock serialization proof). |\n400\t | `test_quota_migration.py` | Migration `0003` (`quotas` table + `api_keys.scope`) round-trip and constraint re-enforcement. |\n401\t | `test_quotas_endpoint.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` integration tests: create/replace, auth, admin-scope enforcement, validation, tenant isolation, rate limiting, OpenAPI exposure. |\n402\t-| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. |\n403\t+| `test_quotas_list_delete.py` | `GET /v1/quotas` and `DELETE /v1/quotas` integration tests: GET ordering + minimal fields, tenant isolation, empty-list 200, ingest-key 403, no-auth 401; DELETE 204 + row removed, 404 on absent, cross-tenant 404 with the victim row intact, validation 422, ingest-key 403, no-auth 401, `quota.delete`/`quota.forbidden` logging; the two-principals-one-IP Tier-2 rate-limit shape on both verbs; the no-usage-reset / uncapped-events-accepted cross-behavior; the safe-error / fail-closed 500 path on both verbs (AC19); a concurrent-DELETE-of-the-same-row race (exactly one winner); and OpenAPI exposure of both new verbs. |\n404\t+| `test_quotas_rls_backstop.py` | Adversarial proof that the `quotas_tenant_isolation` RLS policy alone (connecting as a `NOBYPASSRLS` role, primary `api_key_id` filter removed) still confines reads/updates/deletes to the caller's own tenant, and fails closed when the tenant context is unset. `test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent` (new, quota-admin feature) is the DELETE-specific backstop proof, mirroring the existing read/update cases. |\n405\t | `test_rate_limit.py` | Tier-2 (`api_key_id`-keyed) rate limiting: two principals on one IP get independent buckets; one principal across two IPs shares one bucket. |\n406\t | `test_seed_api_key_script.py` | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` provisions a key against a real database, including the `--admin` flag setting `scope='admin'` (default `scope='ingest'`). |\n407\t | `test_usage_endpoint.py` | `GET /v1/usage` integration tests (aggregation, tenant isolation). |\n408\tdiff --git a/tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py b/tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py\n409\tindex 297093c..3f29b9f 100644\n410\t--- a/tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py\n411\t+++ b/tests/integration/test_quotas_rls_backstop.py\n412\t@@ -130,6 +130,73 @@ async def test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_read_when_app_filter_is_absent(\n413\t         await role_engine.dispose()\n414\t \n415\t \n416\t+async def test_rls_blocks_cross_tenant_delete_when_app_filter_is_absent(\n417\t+    postgres_url, nobypassrls_role, make_api_key\n418\t+):\n419\t+    \"\"\"AC8/AC15 backstop proof for the quota-admin feature's new `DELETE\n420\t+    /v1/quotas` surface: with the explicit `api_key_id` filter entirely\n421\t+    removed from the query (simulating the primary control being\n422\t+    missing/buggy in `quotas_repo.delete_quota`), the RLS policy alone must\n423\t+    still confine a `NOBYPASSRLS` session's DELETE to only its own tenant's\n424\t+    row -- tenant B's row must survive an unfiltered DELETE issued under\n425\t+    tenant A's session setting.\n426\t+    \"\"\"\n427\t+    _, tenant_a_id = await make_api_key(label=\"rls-delete-tenant-a\", scope=\"admin\")\n428\t+    _, tenant_b_id = await make_api_key(label=\"rls-delete-tenant-b\", scope=\"admin\")\n429\t+\n430\t+    admin_engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n431\t+    async with admin_engine.begin() as connection:\n432\t+        await connection.execute(\n433\t+            text(\n434\t+                \"INSERT INTO quotas (api_key_id, customer_id, metric, limit_per_window) \"\n435\t+                \"VALUES (:id, 'rls_del_cust', 'api_calls', 1000)\"\n436\t+            ),\n437\t+            {\"id\": tenant_a_id},\n438\t+        )\n439\t+        await connection.execute(\n440\t+            text(\n441\t+                \"INSERT INTO quotas (api_key_id, customer_id, metric, limit_per_window) \"\n442\t+                \"VALUES (:id, 'rls_del_cust', 'api_calls', 2000)\"\n443\t+            ),\n444\t+            {\"id\": tenant_b_id},\n445\t+        )\n446\t+    await admin_engine.dispose()\n447\t+\n448\t+    role_engine = create_async_engine(nobypassrls_role)\n449\t+    try:\n450\t+        async with role_engine.begin() as connection:\n451\t+            await connection.execute(\n452\t+                text(\"SELECT set_config('app.current_api_key_id', :id, true)\"),\n453\t+                {\"id\": str(tenant_a_id)},\n454\t+            )\n455\t+            # No api_key_id predicate at all -- mirrors delete_quota's DELETE\n456\t+            # statement with its primary WHERE clause stripped out.\n457\t+            result = await connection.execute(\n458\t+                text(\"DELETE FROM quotas WHERE customer_id = 'rls_del_cust' RETURNING api_key_id\")\n459\t+            )\n460\t+            deleted_ids = {row[0] for row in result.fetchall()}\n461\t+        assert deleted_ids == {tenant_a_id}, (\n462\t+            \"an unfiltered DELETE under tenant A's session setting must only \"\n463\t+            f\"remove tenant A's own row; deleted api_key_ids={deleted_ids}\"\n464\t+        )\n465\t+\n466\t+        admin_check_engine = create_async_engine(postgres_url)\n467\t+        async with admin_check_engine.connect() as connection:\n468\t+            survivor = (\n469\t+                await connection.execute(\n470\t+                    text(\n471\t+                        \"SELECT limit_per_window FROM quotas \"\n472\t+                        \"WHERE api_key_id = :id AND customer_id = 'rls_del_cust'\"\n473\t+                    ),\n474\t+                    {\"id\": tenant_b_id},\n475\t+                )\n476\t+            ).mappings().one()\n477\t+        await admin_check_engine.dispose()\n478\t+        assert survivor[\"limit_per_window\"] == 2000, \"tenant B's row must survive the cross-tenant DELETE\"\n479\t+    finally:\n480\t+        await role_engine.dispose()\n481\t+\n482\t+\n483\t async def test_rls_denies_all_rows_when_tenant_setting_is_unset(\n484\t     postgres_url, nobypassrls_role, make_api_key\n485\t ):\n486\tdiff --git a/tests/test_schemas_quotas.py b/tests/test_schemas_quotas.py\n487\tindex a079863..a316414 100644\n488\t--- a/tests/test_schemas_quotas.py\n489\t+++ b/tests/test_schemas_quotas.py\n490\t@@ -1,11 +1,12 @@\n491\t-\"\"\"Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (AC5, AC18).\"\"\"\n492\t+\"\"\"Validation-contract tests for `QuotaPutRequest` (AC5, AC18) and\n493\t+`QuotaDeleteParams` (AC9).\"\"\"\n494\t \n495\t import pytest\n496\t from hypothesis import given\n497\t from hypothesis import strategies as st\n498\t from pydantic import ValidationError\n499\t \n500\t-from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaPutRequest\n501\t+from src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaDeleteParams, QuotaPutRequest\n502\t \n503\t \n504\t def _valid_payload(**overrides) -> dict:\n505\t@@ -89,3 +90,62 @@ def test_property_customer_id_only_ever_accepts_the_allowlist(customer_id):\n506\t     except ValidationError:\n507\t         return\n508\t     assert re.fullmatch(r\"[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,128}\", quota.customer_id)\n509\t+\n510\t+\n511\t+def _valid_delete_params(**overrides) -> dict:\n512\t+    params = {\"customer_id\": \"cust_123\", \"metric\": \"api_calls\"}\n513\t+    params.update(overrides)\n514\t+    return params\n515\t+\n516\t+\n517\t+def test_delete_params_accepts_well_formed_identifiers():\n518\t+    \"\"\"AC9: a valid (customer_id, metric) pair parses with the exact values supplied.\"\"\"\n519\t+    params = QuotaDeleteParams(**_valid_delete_params())\n520\t+    assert params.customer_id == \"cust_123\"\n521\t+    assert params.metric == \"api_calls\"\n522\t+\n523\t+\n524\t+def test_delete_params_rejects_missing_fields():\n525\t+    \"\"\"AC9: both customer_id and metric are required.\"\"\"\n526\t+    with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n527\t+        QuotaDeleteParams(customer_id=\"cust_123\")\n528\t+    with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n529\t+        QuotaDeleteParams(metric=\"api_calls\")\n530\t+\n531\t+\n532\t+def test_delete_params_rejects_unknown_fields_mass_assignment():\n533\t+    \"\"\"AC9: `extra='forbid'` rejects a client-supplied `api_key_id` — the\n534\t+    server alone resolves the tenant from the authenticated principal\n535\t+    (ASVS 15.3.3).\"\"\"\n536\t+    with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n537\t+        QuotaDeleteParams(**_valid_delete_params(api_key_id=999))\n538\t+\n539\t+\n540\t+@pytest.mark.parametrize(\n541\t+    \"customer_id\",\n542\t+    [\"' OR 1=1--\", \"../../etc/passwd\", \"line1\\r\\nline2\", \"a\" * 129, \"\"],\n543\t+)\n544\t+def test_delete_params_rejects_injection_and_oversized_customer_id(customer_id):\n545\t+    \"\"\"AC9: SQLi/path-traversal/CRLF/oversized customer_id is rejected at the\n546\t+    schema boundary and never reaches the DELETE SQL sink.\"\"\"\n547\t+    with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n548\t+        QuotaDeleteParams(**_valid_delete_params(customer_id=customer_id))\n549\t+\n550\t+\n551\t+@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"metric\", [\"' OR 1=1--\", \"a\" * 65, \"\"])\n552\t+def test_delete_params_rejects_invalid_metric(metric):\n553\t+    \"\"\"AC9: injection/oversized metric is rejected at the schema boundary.\"\"\"\n554\t+    with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n555\t+        QuotaDeleteParams(**_valid_delete_params(metric=metric))\n556\t+\n557\t+\n558\t+@given(customer_id=st.text(min_size=1, max_size=300))\n559\t+def test_property_delete_customer_id_only_ever_accepts_the_allowlist(customer_id):\n560\t+    \"\"\"Hypothesis: any customer_id accepted by QuotaDeleteParams matches the anchored allowlist.\"\"\"\n561\t+    import re\n562\t+\n563\t+    try:\n564\t+        params = QuotaDeleteParams(**_valid_delete_params(customer_id=customer_id))\n565\t+    except ValidationError:\n566\t+        return\n567\t+    assert re.fullmatch(r\"[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,128}\", params.customer_id)\n568\t"}]},"uuid":"231b5df2-7d9d-4b8a-97d3-fff1a3446831","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:03:05.556Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2bd81695-e8d4-4443-999c-eab0c1531ba5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
