{"parentUuid":"8342f538-c5a7-456a-8734-946d05e6edf0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b6d534eb-f80d-405a-a05d-4c7eb6280654","agentId":"ac1c3361cb16ecefb","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KhinU7CsKEj4tJMzBRPCmp","type":"tool_result","content":"src\\logging\\__init__.py:6:redaction processor so a secret or raw PII value can never leave the process\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:16:_REDACTED = \"***redacted***\"\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:30:        \"customer_id\",\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:36:def _redact_sensitive_fields(\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:41:    This is the centralized PII/secret-redaction control every log call\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:42:    inherits automatically — call sites never redact ad hoc.\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:62:    the redaction/anti-forging processors, and stdlib logging routed through it.\"\"\"\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:71:            _redact_sensitive_fields,\nsrc\\logging\\__init__.py:92:    redaction and field conventions stay centralized (`code-standards` facade\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:5:Centralized structured logging facade using structlog: request middleware (correlation context), PII redaction processor, and a uniform `get_logger()` entry point for all modules.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:11:| `__init__.py` | `get_logger(service=...)` — returns a logger instance with the given service name; applies PII redaction. Facade entry point for all logging calls. |\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:22:- Imports `structlog` for structured logging and the PII redaction pipeline.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:24:**PII redaction:**\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:25:- The `get_logger` facade applies a redaction processor that scrubs known PII fields from log output.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:26:- Fields redacted: `customer_id`, `api_key_id`, `secret`, `key_id`, `idempotency_key`, and other credential-adjacent data.\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:27:- Redacted values are replaced with a placeholder (e.g., `\"<redacted>\"` or a hash).\nsrc\\logging\\README.md:28:- Tested in `tests/test_logging_redaction.py`: ensures no raw `customer_id` appears in any log output."}]},"uuid":"944bcb2c-c5c9-4746-98cb-443080b0eb63","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:04:59.274Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8342f538-c5a7-456a-8734-946d05e6edf0","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"944bcb2c-c5c9-4746-98cb-443080b0eb63","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac1c3361cb16ecefb","message":{"model":"claude-fable-5","id":"msg_011CcsiRjqJWFoQ1eF8dBQ1K","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"","signature":""}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6787,"cache_read_input_tokens":64831,"output_tokens":5951,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6787},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5951,"cache_read_input_tokens":64831,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6787,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6787,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsiRhLEueU3DAV8YaHPH","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"7f250e4f-ad65-4e3a-b30e-5adcfbbdbe9b","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:06:22.106Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"7f250e4f-ad65-4e3a-b30e-5adcfbbdbe9b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ac1c3361cb16ecefb","message":{"model":"claude-fable-5","id":"msg_011CcsiRjqJWFoQ1eF8dBQ1K","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have full context on the diff, enclosing functions, transaction/isolation semantics, the error boundary, fixtures, and dependency pins. Key verifications: FastAPI 0.133.0 supports `Annotated[Model, Query()]` with `extra=\"forbid\"`; engine is pinned READ COMMITTED so the concurrent-DELETE race resolves to one winner; `monkeypatch.setattr(quota_service, \"list_quotas\"/\"delete_quota\", ...)` targets the correct imported names; redaction list includes `customer_id`; rate-limit budgets (100/sec default) cover the burst tests. The production code paths (route → service → repo, tenant scoping, 404 mapping, envelope handling) check out; the defensible candidates are one scalability gap in prod code and three test-adequacy/brittleness issues.\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"file\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\brett\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\meterly-pipeline-test\\\\src\\\\repositories\\\\quotas_repo.py\",\n    \"line\": 161,\n    \"summary\": \"GET /v1/quotas is fully unpaginated: list_quotas runs an unbounded SELECT and materializes every tenant row via result.mappings().all(), then the service builds a second full list of QuotaResponse objects and FastAPI serializes a third copy.\",\n    \"failure_scenario\": \"An admin key legitimately upserts a large number of quota rows over time (PUT allows arbitrary distinct 128-char customer_id x 64-char metric pairs, no cap on row count per tenant). A single GET /v1/quotas then loads hundreds of thousands of rows into memory across three list copies and emits a multi-MB JSON body, causing high latency/memory pressure on the shared ECS task — a self-inflicted DoS lever behind a single Tier-2-throttled request. Documented as intentional ('full, unpaginated'), but nothing bounds it.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"file\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\brett\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\meterly-pipeline-test\\\\tests\\\\integration\\\\test_quotas_list_delete.py\",\n    \"line\": 350,\n    \"summary\": \"test_delete_and_forbidden_are_logged's redaction assertion is vacuous for the DELETE path: '***redacted***' in captured.out is already satisfied by the seed PUT's quota.upsert log line, and the test never asserts the raw value 'cust_1' is absent.\",\n    \"failure_scenario\": \"If the quota.delete call site regressed to leak a raw customer_id (e.g., logged via a logger that bypasses the redaction processor, or under a renamed key like 'customerId' not in the redaction set), this test would still pass because the earlier quota.upsert line contains the redacted placeholder — the AC16 claim 'customer_id redacted' for quota.delete is not actually proven.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"file\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\brett\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\meterly-pipeline-test\\\\tests\\\\integration\\\\test_quotas_list_delete.py\",\n    \"line\": 413,\n    \"summary\": \"The DELETE fail-closed test monkeypatches quota_service.delete_quota to raise before any SQL executes, so the 'transaction rolls back, target row survives' assertion is trivially true — the DELETE statement never ran, so there was nothing to roll back.\",\n    \"failure_scenario\": \"A real mid-transaction failure mode (exception after the DELETE statement executes but before commit, e.g., a failure in a second statement added later inside the same scoped_transaction) is not exercised; if scoped_transaction ever committed early or the error boundary swallowed the exception post-DELETE, the row would be lost despite a 500, and this test would not catch it. The row-intact assertion at line 448 proves nothing beyond the mock raising early.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"file\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\brett\\\\OneDrive\\\\Documents\\\\GitHub\\\\meterly-pipeline-test\\\\tests\\\\integration\\\\test_quotas_list_delete.py\",\n    \"line\": 506,\n    \"summary\": \"test_no_new_alembic_migration_added hard-codes 'exactly 3 migration files' as a permanent suite invariant rather than a review-time check of this change.\",\n    \"failure_scenario\": \"The very next feature that legitimately adds alembic/versions/0004_*.py breaks this quota-admin test file with a failure unrelated to quota list/delete behavior — a time-bomb assertion that encodes a per-PR acceptance criterion (AC14) as a forever-green test.\"\n  }\n]\n```"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6787,"cache_read_input_tokens":64831,"output_tokens":5951,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6787},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5951,"cache_read_input_tokens":64831,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6787,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6787,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsiRhLEueU3DAV8YaHPH","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"code-review","type":"assistant","uuid":"103e4c20-0896-4ee5-87cb-1aeaf745ddda","timestamp":"2026-07-10T04:06:22.113Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
